# CC PROMPT — v2.27.4 — Frontend: Rotation test modal (RotationTestModal component)

## What this does
New `gui/src/components/RotationTestModal.jsx` — triggered when saving credential changes to a profile.

Flow:
1. User edits profile credentials in ProfileForm → clicks "Update Profile"
2. Instead of immediate save: opens RotationTestModal
3. Modal calls POST /api/credential-profiles/{id}/test-rotation with new_credentials
4. Shows animated list of connections being tested, result per connection
5. All pass → calls /confirm-rotation, modal closes, profiles refresh
6. Some fail → shows list with fail/pass, "Save anyway" button (role-gated)
   - sith_lord: always visible, one click, logged
   - imperial_officer: visible, requires override_reason textarea, logged
   - stormtrooper: not available — sees "Contact administrator" message

Modal is connected from ProfileForm in ConnectionsTab (OptionsModal.jsx).
Version bump: 2.27.3 → 2.27.4

